\r\n[column size=\"half\" last=\"yes\"]\r\n<h3>Sustainability Standards and Metrics</h3>\r\nCFN participants obtain the resources they need to develop practical, functional metrics tailored to their community and its fisheries; help in assessing their needs for data collection that supports harvest and product accountability; and assistance in developing Community Sustainability Plans. <a title=\"Sustainability Standards Outline\" href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/SustainabilityStandardsOutline.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">To see an outline of the Sustainability Standards, click here.</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"10 Solutions to Save the Ocean\" href=\"http://conservationmagazine.org/2008/07/10-solutions-to-save-the-ocean/\" target=\"_blank\">10 Solutions to Save the Ocean - Conversation Magazine, July 29, 2008</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.communityfisheriesnetwork.org/images/McClenachan_etal_2014_CSF_sustainability.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Fisheries Research 157 (2014) 62-69</a>\r\n\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[/columns]\r\n\r\n[accordions]\r\n\r\n[accordion title=\"Seafood Business-Planning\" active=\"yes\"]\r\n\r\nCFN participants have access to one-on-one business planning and development of an informal mentoring network using local resources and national experts acting as senior advisors, along with peer-to-peer learning and online information-sharing.\r\n\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Networking and Marketing\" active=\"yes|no\"]\r\n\r\nCFN participants can share best practices on bycatch, monitoring, evaluation, and other innovations through a peer-to-peer, in-person and remote communications network. They also partner with other Network organizations, and receive technical assistance in video, social-media and other \"storytelling\" platforms and proficiencies to build local support for their efforts and products and reach new audiences across the country. <a href=\"/news/community-fisheries-network-holds-annual-meeting-in-portland-maine/\">Click here to learn more about our third annual meeting.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.mobilisationlab.org/four-magic-steps-to-creating-shareable-purpose-driven-social-media-content/?utm_source=MobLab+Emails&amp;utm_campaign=c85d099f2f-Four_magic_steps_letter12_2013&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_term=0_ce4a881f66-c85d099f2f-66560025\" target=\"_blank\">Four Magic Steps to Creating Shareable, Purpose-Driven Social Media Content by Mob Lab</a>\r\n\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Policy\" active=\"yes|no\"]\r\n\r\nCFN participants have the opportunity to participate in the development and communication of community perspectives on matters of national interest in fisheries management, conservation and economic development policy.\r\n\r\n[/accordion]\r\n\r\n[/accordions]\r\n<h3>Online Archives</h3>\r\nCFN members have exclusive access to archived documents that provide in-depth information in several areas of interest. <a href=\"/wp-login.php\">Click here to access.</a>','Resources','','publish','open','open','','resources','','','2014-09-05 03:22:37','2014-09-05 03:22:37','',0,'http://www.communityfisheriesnetwork.org/?page_id=1149',0,'page','',0),(1150,1,'2014-09-05 02:35:24','2014-09-05 02:35:24','','Resources','','publish','open','open','','1150','','','2014-09-05 02:57:07','2014-09-05 02:57:07','',0,'http://www.communityfisheriesnetwork.org/news/Templates/1150/',0,'pb_template','',0),(1152,1,'2014-09-05 02:37:15','2014-09-05 02:37:15','','Resources','','inherit','open','open','','1149-revision-v1','','','2014-09-05 02:37:15','2014-09-05 02:37:15','',1149,'http://www.communityfisheriesnetwork.org/news/1149-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1153,1,'2014-09-05 03:21:56','2014-09-05 03:21:56','[columns]\n\n[column size=\"half\" last=\"no\"]\n<h3>Organizational Development</h3>\nCFN participants receive high-level advice from local volunteer experts about legal, financial, personnel, board management,and fundraising; relevant information on governance structures, and customized technical a