 England, Collaboration with the Community Fisheries Network &amp;\r\nOther Inspiring Fisheries Organizations[/lead]\r\n\r\nA team from AMCC along with other Alaskan fishing friends embarked on an amazing voyage to Maine and Boston in early March. I accompanied the “Kodiak contingent” which included Dave Kubiak, AMCC’s board chair, Theresa Peterson, AMCC’s Kodiak Outreach Coordinator, and Darius Kasprzak, President of the Alaska Jig Association. All three of the Kodiak group are active fishers, which gave our group lots of “fish cred” to carry with us as we headed east. Linda Behnken, President of the Alaskan Longline Fishermen’s Association and a member of AMCC’s Board of Advisors also went on trip.','Alaska Marine Conservation Counsel Newsletter April 2013','','inherit','open','open','','1263-revision-v1','','','2014-09-05 14:53:54','2014-09-05 14:53:54','',1263,'http://www.communityfisheriesnetwork.org/news/1263-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1265,1,'2014-09-05 14:54:28','2014-09-05 14:54:28','','AMCCNewsletterCFNmeeting','','inherit','open','open','','amccnewslettercfnmeeting','','','2014-09-05 14:54:28','2014-09-05 14:54:28','',0,'http://www.communityfisheriesnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AMCCNewsletterCFNmeeting.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1266,1,'2014-09-05 14:55:58','2014-09-05 14:55:58','<h2>Partnerships for Fisheries Innovation, Growth, and Change</h2>\r\n[lead]An Update on Travels to New England, Collaboration with the Community Fisheries Network &amp;\r\nOther Inspiring Fisheries Organizations[/lead]\r\n\r\nA team from AMCC along with other Alaskan fishing friends embarked on an amazing voyage to Maine and Boston in early March. I accompanied the “Kodiak contingent” which included Dave Kubiak, AMCC’s board chair, Theresa Peterson, AMCC’s Kodiak Outreach Coordinator, and Darius Kasprzak, President of the Alaska Jig Association. All three of the Kodiak group are active fishers, which gave our group lots of “fish cred” to carry with us as we headed east. Linda Behnken, President of the Alaskan Longline Fishermen’s Association and a member of AMCC’s Board of Advisors also went on trip.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AMCCNewsletterCFNmeeting.pdf\">Download the complete newsletter</a>.\r\n\r\n[button url=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AMCCNewsletterCFNmeeting.pdf\" style=\"normal\"]Download PDF[/button]','Alaska Marine Conservation Counsel Newsletter April 2013','','inherit','open','open','','1263-revision-v1','','','2014-09-05 14:55:58','2014-09-05 14:55:58','',1263,'http://www.communityfisheriesnetwork.org/news/1263-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1267,1,'2014-09-05 14:57:15','2014-09-05 14:57:15','<h2>Partnerships for Fisheries Innovation, Growth, and Change</h2>\r\n[lead]An Update on Travels to New England, Collaboration with the Community Fisheries Network &amp;\r\nOther Inspiring Fisheries Organizations[/lead]\r\n\r\nA team from AMCC along with other Alaskan fishing friends embarked on an amazing voyage to Maine and Boston in early March. I accompanied the “Kodiak contingent” which included Dave Kubiak, AMCC’s board chair, Theresa Peterson, AMCC’s Kodiak Outreach Coordinator, and Darius Kasprzak, President of the Alaska Jig Association. All three of the Kodiak group are active fishers, which gave our group lots of “fish cred” to carry with us as we headed east. Linda Behnken, President of the Alaskan Longline Fishermen’s Association and a member of AMCC’s Board of Advisors also went on trip.\r\n\r\n[button url=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AMCCNewsletterCFNmeeting.pdf\" style=\"normal\"]Download PDF[/button]','Alaska Marine Conservation Counsel Newsletter April 2013','','inherit','open','open','','1263-revision-v1','','','2014-09-05 14:57:15','2014-09-05 14:57:15','',1263,'http://www.communityfisheriesnetwork.org/news/1263-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1268,1,'2014-09-05 14:58:08','2014-09-05 14:58:08','','temp_amcc_newsletter','Left to right: D. Kasprzak, T. Peterson, K